--- In junit@yahoogroups.com, &quot;Jamie&quot; &lt;jimbobdobson@h...&gt; wrote:
&gt; I think you want to encapsulate the call to the API that your tests 
use only once.  Although it is usually wise to set up each 
individually test and this is why setUp and tearDown are so handy.  
&gt; 
&gt; However, it you really want to re-use an object throughout your 
tests create them in the constructor.  The class that your tests are 
in will only be instantiated ONCE by the test framework.  Therefore, 
if you want to create an object X once and re-use it in all your 
tests you can do something like this:
&gt; 
&gt; class YourTests extends TestCase
&gt; {
&gt;     public YourTests(String name)
&gt;     {    
&gt;         super(name);
&gt;         // YOUR SET UP CODE HERE
&gt;         TheObjectYouWantToReUse X = new TheObjectYouWantToReUse
();        
&gt;     }    
&gt; 
&gt;     
&gt;     public void testXXX()
&gt;     {
&gt; 
&gt;     }
&gt; }
